### Example 1.4: Arc-Length Parametrization of a Curve

Re-parametrize a curve so that the parameter is distance traveled (`s`) instead of `t`. This is called **arc-length parametrization**.

```scheme
(define (arc-length-param-example)
  (let* ((curve (lambda (t) (list t (* t t))))
         (s-of-t (lambda (t) (calc/arc-length curve 0 t)))
         (total-s (s-of-t 2))
         (t-of-s (lambda (s)
                   (calc/newton
                     (lambda (t) (- (s-of-t t) s))
                     (lambda (t) (curve/speed curve t))
                     (/ s total-s))))  ; initial guess
         (curve-s (lambda (s) (curve (t-of-s s)))))
    (plot/parametric curve-s 0 total-s 100)))
```

[VISUAL: Same parabola, now parametrized by arc length — evenly spaced samples]

<!-- BUILD: run; show side-by-side: original t-parametrization vs. s-parametrization -->

