### Example 2.3: Acceleration Components — Tangential and Normal

Acceleration decomposes into **tangential** (along the velocity) and **normal** (perpendicular, toward the curve's center of curvature).

```scheme
(define (accel-decomposition-example)
  (let* ((r (lambda (t) (list t (* t t))))
         (v (curve/velocity r))
         (a (curve/accel r))
         (speed (curve/speed r))
         (T (curve/unit-tangent r))
         (t0 1)
         (v-val (v t0))
         (a-val (a t0))
         (T-val (T t0))
         (a-tangent (* (vec/dot a-val T-val) 1))  ; scalar
         (a-normal-vec (vec/- a-val (vec/scale T-val a-tangent))))
    (list 'at-t=1
          (list 'acceleration a-val)
          (list 'tangent-component a-tangent)
          (list 'normal-component (vec/norm a-normal-vec)))))
```

[VISUAL: Diagram of curve at t=1 with acceleration vector decomposed into tangent and normal parts]

<!-- BUILD: run; display as annotated vector diagram -->

