## 3. Curvature in 2D — How Sharply a Curve Turns

The **curvature** κ (kappa) measures how sharply a curve bends. For a plane curve **r(t) = (x(t), y(t))**:

**κ = |x' y'' - y' x''| / (x'² + y'²)^(3/2)**

A straight line has κ = 0; a circle of radius R has κ = 1/R.

### Example 3.1: Curvature of a Circle

```scheme
(define (circle-curvature-example)
  (let* ((r 7)
         (circle (lambda (t)
                   (list (* r (geom/cos t))
                         (* r (geom/sin t)))))
         (kappa (curve/curvature-2d circle)))
    (list 'curvature-at-t=0 (kappa 0)
          'expected (/ 1 r))))
```

[VISUAL: Number line comparing computed curvature to 1/r ≈ 0.1428]

<!-- BUILD: run; display as number line -->

