### Example 3.3: Radius of Curvature — The Osculating Circle

The **radius of curvature** is R = 1/κ. The **osculating circle** at a point is the circle of radius R that best fits the curve there.

```scheme
(define (osculating-circle-example)
  (let* ((r (lambda (t) (list t (* t t))))
         (t0 1)
         (pt (r t0))
         (osc (curve/osculating-circle r t0)))
    (list 'point pt
          'osculating-circle osc)))
```

[VISUAL: Cartesian plot of parabola with osculating circle drawn at t=1]

