## 5. Splines — The Practical Curves of Design

A **spline** is a piecewise-polynomial curve passing through or near a set of control points. They're the workhorses of computer graphics and CAD.

### Example 5.1: Bézier Curve — Cubic in 2D

A cubic Bézier curve is defined by four control points **P0, P1, P2, P3**:

**B(t) = (1-t)³ P0 + 3(1-t)² t P1 + 3(1-t) t² P2 + t³ P3**

```scheme
(define (bezier-example)
  (let* ((P0 '(0 0))
         (P1 '(1 2))
         (P2 '(3 2))
         (P3 '(4 0))
         (curve (curve/bezier (list P0 P1 P2 P3))))
    (plot/parametric curve 0 1 100)))
```

[VISUAL: Cartesian plot of Bézier curve with control points marked]

<!-- BUILD: run; plot curve + control polygon -->

---

### Example 5.2: Evaluating a Bézier at a Specific t

```scheme
(define (bezier-eval-example)
  (let* ((P0 '(0 0))
         (P1 '(1 3))
         (P2 '(2 3))
         (P3 '(3 0))
         (curve (curve/bezier (list P0 P1 P2 P3)))
         (pt-at-half (curve/bezier-eval (list P0 P1 P2 P3) 0.5)))
    (list 'point-at-t=0.5 pt-at-half)))
```

