### Example 5.3: Hermite Spline — Specifying Positions and Tangents

A Hermite spline interpolates two points with specified tangent vectors at each.

```scheme
(define (hermite-example)
  (let* ((P0 '(0 0))
         (P1 '(3 2))
         (T0 '(1 1))   ; tangent at P0
         (T1 '(1 -1))  ; tangent at P1
         (curve (curve/hermite P0 T0 P1 T1)))
    (plot/parametric curve 0 1 100)))
```

