## 8. Advanced Topics — Christoffel Symbols, Euler-Lagrange, and More

These are the deep-end tools — where differential geometry meets physics and the calculus of variations.

### Example 8.1: Christoffel Symbols on a Surface

The **Christoffel symbols** encode how the coordinate system curves with the surface.

```scheme
(define (christoffel-example)
  (let* ((f (lambda (x y) (* x y)))
         (surface (curve/surface-graph f))
         (pt '(1 1))
         (gamma (curve/christoffel surface pt)))
    gamma))
```

