### Example 8.8: Frenet Frame Rotation Rate

The angular velocity of the Frenet frame is related to curvature and torsion.

```scheme
(define (frenet-rotation-example)
  (let* ((helix (lambda (t)
                  (list (geom/cos t)
                        (geom/sin t)
                        t)))
         (kappa (curve/curvature helix))
         (tau (curve/torsion helix))
         (t0 1)
         (omega-magnitude (math/pow (+ (* (kappa t0) (kappa t0))
                                       (* (tau t0) (tau t0)))
                                     0.5)))
    (list 'angular-velocity-magnitude omega-magnitude)))
```

